[bq="toxicrystal"]"@uc9":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/55987fa8636872783c000347#post_55987fa8636872783c000347
So wait, what does this mean for the rest of the world?[/bq]
Rest of the world:
!http://cdn.meme.am/instances/500x/24907317.jpg!

China is the third largest economy in the world; while their economy falling doesn't immediately impact the world as a whole rapidly it will in the long run mean that the economy will be negatively impacted by all the businesses they own and debt they own.

China failing = economic stagnation as a whole

Greece's talks breaking down means a chain reaction for Europe since most countries use the Euro.  Best case scenario: economic stagnation in europe.  Worst case scenario: the european union breakes up.


Tl:dr; best case scenario: economic stagnation and all the economic growth stops.  worst case scenario: another recession.
